nodes.documentation:
@dev Add a value to a setMapping. O(1).
Returns false if the value was already in the setMapping.
nodes.name: addValueForKey

nodes.documentation:
@dev Removes a value from a setMapping. O(1).
Returns false if the value was not present in the setMapping.
nodes.name: removeValueForKey

typeDescriptions.typeString: function (struct EnumerableSet.Set storage pointer,bytes32) view returns (bool)

nodes.documentation: @dev Returns true if the value is in the setMapping. O(1).
nodes.name: containsValueForKey

typeDescriptions.typeString: function (struct EnumerableSet.Set storage pointer) view returns (bytes32[] memory)

nodes.documentation:
@dev Returns an array with all values in the setMapping. O(N).
Note that there are no guarantees on the ordering of values inside the
array, and it may change when more values are added or removed.
WARNING: This function may run out of gas on large setMappings: use {length} and
{get} instead in these cases.
nodes.name: enumerateForKey

typeDescriptions.typeString: function (struct EnumerableSet.Set storage pointer) view returns (uint256)

nodes.documentation: @dev Returns the number of elements on the setMapping. O(1).
nodes.name: lengthForKey

typeDescriptions.typeString: function (struct EnumerableSet.Set storage pointer,uint256) view returns (bytes32)

nodes.documentation:
@dev Returns the element stored at position `index` in the setMapping. O(1).
Note that there are no guarantees on the ordering of values inside the
array, and it may change when more values are added or removed.
    * Requirements:
    * - `index` must be strictly less than {length}.
nodes.name: getValueAtIndexForKey
